# Fly.io-specific build exclusions (in addition to .dockerignore)
# Further reduces build context size

# Development files
*.md
!README.md
CHANGELOG*
CONTRIBUTING*
DEVELOPMENT*

# Test data and fixtures
**/test_*.py
**/tests/fixtures/**
**/tests/data/**
frontend/test/**

# Large assets not needed in build
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.gif
*.svg
!frontend/public/favicon.ico

# Build artifacts (already handled by .dockerignore but double-sure)
frontend/.vite/
frontend/tsconfig.tsbuildinfo

# Documentation folders
docs/
.planning/
examples/
